<br>
However I would tend to agree - that unless extended the duration of the cast illusion it would be pretty pointless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/urubicantdeluness.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rubicant DeLuness</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#330000>(4/30/02 1:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/twinr00bycloseup1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Permanent Illusion</span><hr size=1> For those that are wondering, I went ahead and trained in the skill just to try it out.  I hit dark elf illusion and ran across a zone line to check.  Sure enough, the illusion buff remained in place.<br>
<br>
But, when I panned out in a 3rd person view, I saw myself as a high elf (my starting race).  Did a /who on myself, it listed me as a high elf.  Asked the person standing next to me what race I looked like - Dark Elf.  So... it seems to be bugged client-side: PC's still see your illusion and NPC's still see it as well (useful to remember when I went back to Felwithe... oops), but you cannot see it yourself (similar to, for example, getting shroomed in FG - when you break out of mushroom form, hence dropping an illusion, it drops you out of your other illusion as well, tho the buff remains in place).<br>
<br>
As for duration, it seems to last until (a) I die or (b) I get dispelled.  I quit timing it after about 2 hours, and frankly, I don't think I ever manage to go for 8-12 hours without (a) dying or (b) getting dispelled, so I can't comment on whether it's really permanent or whether permanence is 8-12 hours but... for what it is, it's good enough for me.<br>
<br>
I always wished I'd made my chanter a dark elf, and this is about the closest I can come to making that happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
